comment_data.body:
After looking at this for a while, I think this can be greatly simplified.

First a quick question, do we need the call to `PyObject_Dir` if we already have the module dictionary? Internally `PyObject_Dir` will call `moduleobject.c:module_dir` which ends up calling `PyDict_Keys` of the internal module dictionary. This will exactly match the keys from the module dict that we already have. At least this is what happens in CPython master (and 3.8, 3.7, and 3.6). Maybe some older version did not do the same?

Thus, what about changing this to:
```
static PyObject* __Pyx_Globals(void) {
    PyObject *globals;
#if CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
    globals = PyModule_GetDict($module_cname);
    if (unlikely(!globals)) return NULL;
#else
    globals = $moddict_cname;
#endif
    Py_INCREF(globals);
    return globals;
}
```

I could even add a separate PR to simplify this `__Pyx_Globals` first and then this PR can add the `LIMITED_API` change.

Thoughts? All tests are passing with the proposed change

